  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dad\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0dad \u0dbd\u0dd9\u0dc3 \u0d8b\u0daf\u0dca\u0db0\u0db8\u0db1\u0dba \u0d89\u0dc4\u0dc5\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Inflation hits record highs",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Bloomberg website says that there has been hyperinflation in Sri Lanka.",
        "Inflation in Sri Lanka rose to 54.6 percent in June, according to a Bloomberg website.",
        "The Bloomberg website previously reported that June inflation was 43.7 percent, citing data from a survey of Bloomberg economists.",
        "According to the Bloomberg website, Sri Lanka has easily passed the 50 percent threshold, which many economists call the hyperinflation threshold.",
        "Surface inflation, measured by the annual point change in the Colombo Consumer Price Index, was 39.1 percent in May and rose to 54.6 percent in June. The monthly change in June was 12.8 percent. 6.81 percent increase and 5.99 percent increase in prices of non-food category items.",
        "According to economists, the rise in annual point inflation was due to a monthly increase in the prices of food and non - food items.",
        "Inflation in Sri Lanka's food category in May was 57.4 percent and increased to 80.1 percent in June. Inflation in non-food category was 30.6 percent in May and it was recorded as 42.4 percent in June.",
        "According to the Bloomberg website, Sri Lanka is facing a shortage of items in food and non-food categories due to the lack of foreign reserves to import.",
        "Prices of fish, vegetables, bakery products, rice and milk powder rose in June. This has led to an increase in food inflation. Rising fuel prices, transport and bus fares, mainly in the non-food category, contributed to the rise in non-food inflation.",
        "Core inflation in the Colombo Consumer Price Index on an annualized point basis was 28.4 percent in May, rising to 39.9 percent in June."
      ],
